st-income%20households%20could%20simply%20stop%20buying%20any%20wine%2C%20as%20it's%20a%20luxury%20they%20don't%20need%20amid%20the%20economic%20turmoil.%20Still%2C%20mid-range%20varietals%2C%20like%20those%20abundant%20in%20California%2C%20have%20a%20narrow%20opportunity%20to%20gain%20ground%2C%20both%20in%20direct%20sales%20and%20tourism%20to%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20feel%20like%20if%20people%20are%20pulling%20their%20purse%20strings%20because%20of%20their%20worries%20about%20the%20economy%2C%20then%20they%20would%20typically%20%E2%80%94%20and%20we%20saw%20this%20certainly%20during%20COVID%20but%20for%20other%20different%20reasons%20%E2%80%94%20choose%20to%20come%20to%20Santa%20Barbara%20County%20versus%20taking%20European%20vacations%2C%26quot%3B%20Scott%20Bull%2C%20owner%20of%20Sustainable%20Wine%20Tours%20in%20Santa%20Barbara%2C%20California%2C%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we're%20talking%20about%20wine%20enthusiasts%20in%20general%2C%20we've%20seen%20they%20will%20turn%20to%20the%20California%20market%20to%20visit%20their%20local%20backyard%20rather%20than%20taking%20these%20extravagant%20trips.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220a0aff28-837a-43aa-a7a2-e70641be3f37%5C%22%3EA%20boon%20for%20mid-market%20producers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECalifornia%20produces%20an%20average%20of%2081%25%20of%20total%20US%20wine%2C%20employs%201.1%20million%20Americans%2C%20and%20generates%20%24170.5%20billion%20in%20annual%20economic%20activity%20across%20the%20country%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwineinstitute.org%2Four-industry%2Fstatistics%2Fcalifornia-us-wine-production%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWine%20Institute%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20famous%20Napa%20Valley%2C%20located%20northeast%20of%20San%20Francisco%2C%20is%20a%20major%20tourism%20draw%2C%20as%20is%20Santa%20Barbara%20County%20on%20the%20Central%20Coast%20and%20the%20Southern%20California%20wine%20region%20of%20the%20Temecula%20Valley.